$ System.DateTimeOffset (struct)

An instance of `System.DateTimeOffset` represents a point in time relative to the → misc/UTC[Coordinated Universal Time (UTC)] and stores an instance of
  • a → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/DateTime[`System.DateTime`] object (which represents the point in time) and
  • a → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/TimeSpan[`System.TimeSpan`] object (which represents the offset between the point in time and the UTC).

The value of the offset is between -14 and 14 hours and has an accuracy of minutes.

sa:

  → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/DateTime[`System.DateTime`]

  The → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types[SQL Server data type] that is suited best to store a `DateTimeOffset` is
  → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types/datetimeoffset[`datetimeoffset`].
